The deeper pattern (this is your lane)

You’re really describing:

Speech needs a “keep-alive signal.”

Like networking:
	•	If you stop sending packets → connection drops
	•	Fillers = heartbeat packets

So people reach for whatever maintains:
	•	rhythm
	•	attention
	•	conversational control

If they don’t have a clean zero token, they borrow from:
	•	emotion (swearing)
	•	identity (slang)
	•	habit (like/you know)

⸻

A practical upgrade (real-world usable)

If you actually want to implement this in your own speech:

Use a 3-layer system:
	•	Level 1 (pure buffer): “mm”, “eh”
	•	Level 2 (neutral bridge): “right”, “so”
	•	Level 3 (intent marker): “hold on”, “let me think”

Example:

“So—mm—right—I think what’s happening is…”

This keeps:
	•	cadence
	•	clarity
	•	control

without importing baggage.

